Create partition.yaml, which ll create partitions on managed nodes:

- After sdb creating a 1000M primary partition, partition number 1, and format ext4

- prod group to permanently mount the partition to /data

- If there is not enough disk space, give prompt information

"Could not create partition of that size"

- Create 800M partition

- If sdb does not exist, a prompt message will be given

" this disk does not exists"
